The Intercontinental Ballistic Missile (ICBM) market has demonstrated notable resilience and strategic importance within the global defense sector. As of the latest assessment, the market valuation stands at approximately USD 15 billion, reflecting steady growth driven by geopolitical tensions, technological advancements, and modernization initiatives across key defense budgets. Historically, the market has experienced a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of around 4.5% over the past five years, underpinned by increased investments in strategic deterrence capabilities.

